        <p>An Oil to Make Scallops</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>It takes only a few drops of grilled almond oil from Huileries de Lapalisse in France to give seared sea scallops, grilled chicken salad, slices of ripe pear or a piece of aged pecorino cheese a touch of extraordinary flavor and aroma. The oil is a condiment and is meant to add a finishing touch, much like Asian toasted sesame oil. It costs $6.49 for a 250-milliliter bottle (almost nine ounces) at Fairway markets.</p>
      </block>
